# 🚀 DevOps CI/CD Pipeline Project (Node.js + Docker + Jenkins)

## 📌 Overview
This project demonstrates an end-to-end DevOps CI/CD pipeline using Jenkins, Docker, and AWS. It automates the process of building, containerizing, and deploying a Node.js application to ensure faster and reliable delivery.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- Node.js (Application)
- Docker (Containerization)
- Jenkins (CI/CD Automation)
- AWS EC2 (Deployment)
- GitHub (Version Control)

---

## 🔄 CI/CD Pipeline Workflow

1. Developer pushes code to GitHub  
2. Jenkins triggers pipeline automatically  
3. Jenkins pulls latest code  
4. Docker image is built using Dockerfile  
5. Container is deployed on server  
6. Application becomes accessible  

---

## ⚙️ Jenkins Pipeline

The pipeline is defined using a **Jenkinsfile** and performs:

- Code checkout from GitHub  
- Build process automation  
- Docker image creation  
- Container deployment  

---

## 🐳 Docker Implementation

Docker is used to containerize the Node.js application, ensuring consistency across environments.

### Commands Used:
```bash
docker build -t node-app .
docker run -d -p 3000:3000 node-app
